Insights - Reports and Studies






 

					21.06.17				



Where is the neutral monetary policy? Nordic currencies to strengthen?
"...If this were true, it would imply that the neutral policy rate for Norway and Sweden would be higher than that for the eurozone, which in turn would be likely to lead to a potential strengthening of their currencies. Higher expected long-term growth and stronger currency indeed makes the Nordics an attractive environment for investors."






 

					10.03.17				



Nordic High Yield – Why we think this market is interesting now
The Nordic High Yield market has been through a rough ride since 2014 with the falling oil price leading to massive defaults and restructurings in the energy sector.

 

What about now, is it time to come back to the Nordic High Yield market?

 



