Our executive committee - Alfred Berg






































































 
 









 


Home / Alfred Berg, a modern asset manager with tradition / Our executive committee






Our executive committee 








Vincent Trouillard-Perrot
Nordic CEO, Alfred Berg
Vincent Trouillard-Perrot is the Nordic CEO of Alfred Berg, with the overall responsibility for the business development of Alfred Berg in the Nordic and Baltic markets. He has over 20 years’ experience in the European and Asian financial markets. Prior to joining Alfred Berg in 2011 Vincent served as CEO HK and head of APAC Hub at BNP Paribas Investment Partners in Asia. His previous experience includes several years in the Asian asset management industry.
Vincent holds a master’s degree in finance, marketing and business administration from INSEEC Paris School of Business.




Helge S. Arnesen
Nordic CIO, Alfred Berg
Helge S. Arnesen is the managing director of Alfred Berg Asset Management AS in Norway and CIO with overall responsibility for Alfred Berg’s investments in the Nordic market. Helge has been employed at Alfred Berg since 2010 and has over 20 years’ experience in the Norwegian financial market. He came from a position of fixed income manager and a member of the investment committee of Folketrygdfondet, part of the Norwegian Government Pension Fund. His previous experience includes 10 years at Life Insurance, and several years as fixed income trader and portfolio manager.
Helge received his master’s degree in industrial economics from NTNU, and has also received master’s degree in technology management from NTNU/NHH/MIT.



Juhani Keinänen
Country Manager & Head of Sales, Alfed Berg Finland
Juhani Keinänen is the country manager in Finland, also heading the local sales function. Juhani joined Alfred Berg in 2015. He started his career in finance in 1988, and has branch experience from multiple posts related to client relationships and portfolio management. Prior to Alfred Berg he worked for Danske Capital, Carnegie, Opstock, DNB and Merita-Norbanken (Nordea). Juhani has also lived and worked in Norway for seven years.Juhani holds an MBA from Svenska Handelshögskolan in Helsinki.




Serge Riff
Nordic CFO, Alfred Berg
Serge Riff is the Nordic chief financial officer of the Alfred Berg Group since July 2011. Previously he was deputy group chief financial officer for BNP Paribas Investment Partners, the mother company of Alfred Berg. Serge has been with BNP Paribas since 1990. After various positions in IT and within the Internal Audit teams, he joined BNPP Investment Partners in 2001 to become global head of management accounting.
Serge received his master’s degree from Ecole Centrale de Lille.




Tomas Scherp
CEO, Alfred Berg Kapitalförvaltning AB
Tomas Scherp is CEO of Alfred Berg Kapitalförvaltning AB and the Nordic Head of Sales. Tomas has more than 19 years’ experience in the financial market. He joined Alfred Berg in 2000. Prior to his present position he has had several different roles in the Swedish and the Nordic organization starting from product and business development after which he has been engaged in the sales organization. Before joining Alfred Berg, Tomas worked as senior consultant specialized in asset management.
Tomas holds a master’s degree in business studies and economics as well as a Certified European Financial Analyst (CEFA) diploma.




Elisabeth Stejmar
Nordic Head of HR, Alfred Berg
Elisabeth Stejmar is the Nordic Head of HR at Alfred Berg Asset Management AB in Sweden. Elisabeth takes overall responsibility for HR in the Nordic region. She has over 20 years’ experience in the Nordic HR of the financial market.  Prior to joining Alfred Berg in 2012, Elisabeth worked as head of HR at RBS, Xaar and ABB Treasury Center. Her previous experience includes 20 years in the branch in different positions.



 








